ll of Li He's poetry, in facing-page format with the original texts, with explanatory notes on literary and historical references and difficult points of interpretation, along with endnotes briefly discussing textual variants and other technical matters. Taken together, these features will be a welcome aid to readers wishing to explore Li He's poetic worlds first-hand.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Tang Prize Foundation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh  aLi He (790-816).  aTang dynasty (618-907) Poetry.1 aAllen, Sarah M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNugent, Christopher M. B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTian, Xiaofei, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aTang Prize Foundationefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2023z978311120579308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015046930 cprintz978150151329940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501504716zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501504716zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyte